      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Those words show the profound exhaustion you feel, and many conversations with professional counselors can help you sit with that grief without having to perform or pretend anything is better. Because the comparison to a lost sun is so powerful, look for a therapist who specializes in complicated grief to validate that it is okay not to feel like anything is right again right now. You are not failing by not being able to see a \"light\" yet; you are simply navigating a very dark, very heavy landscape that deserves deep, unfiltered support.",
